                     (subject to there being a large number of information seekers). We focus here on what happens when there is a purchase of shares at time 1.

sec.p:
The information seekers are in the market at time 2. Given that the information seekers observe the trading activity at time 1, they know that the informed party has good information about the firm’s prospects (
                  \documentclass{aastex} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{bm} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{pifont} \usepackage{stmaryrd} \usepackage{textcomp} \usepackage{portland,xspace} \usepackage{amsmath,amsxtra} \usepackage[OT2,OT1]{fontenc} \newcommand\cyr{ \renewcommand\rmdefault{wncyr} \renewcommand\sfdefault{wncyss} \renewcommand\encodingdefault{OT2} \normalfont \selectfont} \DeclareTextFontCommand{\textcyr}{\cyr} \pagestyle{empty} \DeclareMathSizes{10}{9}{7}{6} \begin{document} \landscape $V_{H}$ \end{document}
               ) if they observe shares being purchased. Each information seeker also knows that she is competing against the other
